# Advanced Weather App React

A modern weather application built with React that provides detailed weather information and forecasts.

## Features

- Real-time weather data display
- 5-day weather forecast
- Search for weather by city name
- Responsive design for all devices
- Temperature units conversion (Celsius/Fahrenheit)
- Weather conditions visualization
- Wind speed and humidity information

## Project Structure

```
Advanced-Weather_App_react/
├── public/
│   ├── index.html
│   └── assets/
├── src/
│   ├── components/
│   │   ├── CurrentWeather/
│   │   ├── Forecast/
│   │   ├── Search/
│   │   └── WeatherCard/
│   ├── services/
│   │   └── api/
│   ├── utils/
│   ├── styles/
│   ├── App.js
│   └── index.js
└── package.json
```

## Technologies Used

- React.js
- JavaScript/ES6+
- CSS3/SCSS
- Weather API
- Axios for API requests
- React Icons

## Getting Started

1. Clone the repository:
```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/Advanced-Weather_App_react.git
```

2. Install dependencies:
```bash
npm install
```

3. Create a `.env` file and add your Weather API key:
```
REACT_APP_API_KEY=your_api_key_here
```

4. Start the development server:
```bash
npm start
```

## Available Scripts

- `npm start` - Runs the app in development mode
- `npm test` - Launches the test runner
- `npm run build` - Builds the app for production
- `npm run eject` - Ejects from Create React App

